00:05:18.200 --> 00:05:20.920
is when I really started to leverage them more

00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:24.200
for kind of simple tasks like we talked about today.

00:05:24.200 --> 00:05:25.920
It's like a data access.

00:05:25.920 --> 00:05:28.119
And so based on my readings,

00:05:28.119 --> 00:05:30.079
for data access,

00:05:30.079 --> 00:05:32.559
a lot of times we use these kind of post requests

00:05:32.559 --> 00:05:34.320
or get requests,

00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:35.760
but there's so many other different ways

00:05:35.760 --> 00:05:37.359
that you can ping an API.

00:05:37.359 --> 00:05:39.480
And depending on what you're receiving,

00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:42.559
you may want to adjust kind of what you want to say.

00:05:42.559 --> 00:05:44.399
So I know there's a bunch of other options out there

00:05:44.399 --> 00:05:46.839
depending on what your API is going to be doing.

00:05:46.839 --> 00:05:48.359
And so I would just say,

00:05:48.359 --> 00:05:50.239
it might just be worth doing a little bit of research

00:05:50.239 --> 00:05:53.519
to make sure that you're using the right type of request

00:05:53.519 --> 00:05:54.799
from an API,

00:05:54.799 --> 00:05:56.799
depending on how you're interacting with it.

